div.h2: Write Ordering Guarantees Consistent State After Any Crash

div.p: Journal must be durable BEFORE database is modified
Bytes 0-2048: New data Bytes 2049-4095: Old data
Result: Corrupt page structure Invalid cell pointers Broken B-tree invariants
if not exists(journal_path): return // No recovery needed
The order of writes guarantees consistency:

ol.li: Then modify DB Can always undo
Delete journal last Commit is final

div.p: This is the WAL protocol (Write-Ahead Logging):

blockquote.p: "Never modify a page until its original contents have been logged to stable storage"

div.p: This is why transactions feel "slow" - durability has a real cost.
